*Workaround*
Since this only affects JIRA Cloud, please raise a support ticket at support.atlassian.com and reference this bug ticket for the support engineers to resolve this issue.

Deleting projects that have a big number of issues takes some time and causes timeouts in OnDemand. Result: an electric charlie or a "Page unavailable" error screen. As a result, indexes for the deleted project stay in place, and it's still visible under *JIRA Admin > Projects*. Another attempt to delete it results in an error:
{noformat}Exception removing project: Error removing issues: java.lang.NullPointerException{noformat}

*Workaround:* fully reindex JIRA to remove traces of the deleted project (background reindexing times out in the UI, and doesn't remove the deleted project).

